  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed roof extension along with associated screening by reason of its inappropriate detailed design, prominent siting, scale, visibility, massing, bulk and height would result in a dominant and discordant addition to the host building, wider setting of the area. The proposed development would erode the existing rhythm of the roofs on the rear of Blackstock Road and would be seen as a harmful feature when observed from both the public and private realms.  The proposed development is therefore contrary to the NPPF (2021), Policies D1 and D4 of the London Plan (2021), Islington's Urban Design Guide (2017) & Islington Local Plan Policy PLAN 1 (Site appraisal, design principles and process)."
